_Knibb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Knibb\"}, {\"begin\": 513, \"end\": 518, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999998864655091, \"rank\": 1.1353455321904249e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Knibb was the surprise winner of the women's individual time trialat theUSA Cycling Pro Road National Championshipsin May, earning an automatic qualification for both the time trial and road race at theParis Olympics.\", \"from\": 521, \"to\": 738, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 521, \"end\": 526, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Knibb\", \"score\": 0.9993327369604219, \"rank\": 0.0006677085769444153, \"text\": \"Knibb\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Knibb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Knibb\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, Knibb lacks any international mass-start road racing experience.\", \"from\": 740, \"to\": 813, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 749, \"end\": 754, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Knibb\", \"score\": 0.9993327369604219, \"rank\": 0.0006677085769444153, \"text\": \"Knibb\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Knibb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Knibb\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kristen Faulkner, winner of two stages of the Giro Donne and a stage of the Vuelta a Espa\\u00f1a, is the reigning US road race champion, and was selected to replace Knibb after making the US Olympic team for track cycling.\", \"from\": 814, \"to\": 1031, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 814, \"end\": 830, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kristen_Faulkner\", \"score\": 0.9999993389976591, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kristen Faulkner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"]